The paper discusses the need for a consistent model for visually representing the architecture of AI systems, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses challenges related to interpretability and correctness, which are relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and software engineering (cs.SE). The creation of a common diagrammatic language for AI systems also involves system and control theory (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG).
